(VOCALIZES)

1347
01:16:19,389 --> 01:16:25,972
God rest ye merry gentlemen
Let nothing you dismay

1348
01:16:26,097 --> 01:16:27,972
FRAT BRO 1:
Yo, grab that door?

1349
01:16:29,097 --> 01:16:31,222
-(DOOR OPENS)
-FRAT BRO 2: Here we go.

1350
01:16:31,347 --> 01:16:32,139
Thank you.

1351
01:16:32,222 --> 01:16:34,389
That is wicked!

1352
01:16:34,472 --> 01:16:35,639
FRAT BRO 1:
Kegs here!

1353
01:16:35,723 --> 01:16:38,639
(FRAT BRO 1 CHANTING)

1354
01:16:38,723 --> 01:16:39,639
(CHEERING AND CLAPPING)

1355
01:16:42,264 --> 01:16:42,890
SIENNA:
Oh.

1356
01:16:42,972 --> 01:16:44,598
Something smells amazing.

1357
01:16:45,598 --> 01:16:46,848
You're back late.

1358
01:16:46,972 --> 01:16:48,097
How's your brother?

1359
01:16:48,222 --> 01:16:49,347
Oh, he's good.

1360
01:16:49,389 --> 01:16:50,014
Yeah.

1361
01:16:50,097 --> 01:16:51,097
(CLICKS TONGUE)

1362
01:16:51,222 --> 01:16:53,222
He's going to a campus
Christmas party tonight.

1363
01:16:53,347 --> 01:16:55,097
Jonathan's going
to a Christmas party?

1364
01:16:55,972 --> 01:16:56,764
Oh!

1365
01:16:56,848 --> 01:16:58,222
Nice to hear
he's socializing.

1366
01:16:58,264 --> 01:16:59,639
Yeah.

1367
01:17:00,472 --> 01:17:02,764
God, these are so freaking cute,
Aunt Jess.

1368
01:17:03,347 --> 01:17:04,472
Those are my favorite.

1369
01:17:04,598 --> 01:17:05,723
Do you want some?

1370
01:17:06,598 --> 01:17:08,264
No, thanks.

1371
01:17:08,347 --> 01:17:11,222
Oh, sorry, I forgot you don't
like cereal anymore.

1372
01:17:11,347 --> 01:17:12,472
Who doesn't like cereal?

1373
01:17:12,598 --> 01:17:13,347
GABBIE:
Sienna.

1374
01:17:13,472 --> 01:17:16,097
What? Sienna,
you don't like cereal?

1375
01:17:17,097 --> 01:17:20,014
I mean, I can understand tofu
or Lima beans,

1376
01:17:20,097 --> 01:17:20,890
but cereal's the best.

1377
01:17:20,972 --> 01:17:22,347
I know, honey. Chill.

1378
01:17:22,472 --> 01:17:25,139
Yeah, I just try to stay away
from too much sugar.

1379
01:17:25,222 --> 01:17:26,723
GREG:
You got more willpower than me.

1380
01:17:26,764 --> 01:17:28,848
Hey Gabs, what do you say
we go upstairs

1381
01:17:28,972 --> 01:17:31,014
and play some board games?

1382
01:17:31,097 --> 01:17:32,347
Let's go.

1383
01:17:33,472 --> 01:17:34,472
Yeah.

1384
01:17:34,598 --> 01:17:36,472
I think we need some
Christmas tree sprinkles.

1385
01:17:36,514 --> 01:17:38,222
You need
Christmas tree sprinkles.

1386
01:17:38,264 --> 01:17:39,347
What are you in the mood for?

1387
01:17:39,472 --> 01:17:40,514
I have a ton.

1388
01:17:40,598 --> 01:17:44,014
Pictionary,
Guess Who, Monopoly.

1389
01:17:44,097 --> 01:17:45,389
I like Monopoly.

1390
01:17:45,472 --> 01:17:48,014
Takes forever, though.

1391
01:17:48,097 --> 01:17:53,138
I never told you
I don't like cereal.

1392
01:17:53,221 --> 01:17:56,096
What?

1393
01:17:56,221 --> 01:17:58,346
How'd you know
I don't like cereal?

1394
01:18:02,346 --> 01:18:04,889
Gabbie?

1395
01:18:04,971 --> 01:18:06,346
Did you read my journal?

1396
01:18:06,471 --> 01:18:07,722
I'm sorry.

1397
01:18:08,847 --> 01:18:10,597
Please don't be mad at me.

1398
01:18:13,722 --> 01:18:14,471
Where is it?

1399
01:18:14,597 --> 01:18:15,889
I put it back in your room.

1400
01:18:15,971 --> 01:18:17,388
How much of it did you read?

1401
01:18:18,847 --> 01:18:20,221
Tell me.

1402
01:18:20,346 --> 01:18:21,722
All of it?

1403
01:18:22,597 --> 01:18:23,597
Jesus, Gabbie.

1404
01:18:23,722 --> 01:18:26,971
You-- you promised me.

1405
01:18:27,096 --> 01:18:27,971
I'm sorry.

1406
01:18:28,013 --> 01:18:30,013
I wanted to know
what happened to you.

1407
01:18:31,096 --> 01:18:32,597
Is it true?

1408
01:18:32,722 --> 01:18:36,513
All that stuff about
the clown and Uncle Michael?

1409
01:18:37,388 --> 01:18:39,138
You saw him today,
didn't you?

1410
01:18:39,763 --> 01:18:40,471
At the mall.

1411
01:18:40,513 --> 01:18:42,013
That's why you freaked out.

1412
01:18:43,971 --> 01:18:45,597
Gabbie, I'm sick.

1413
01:18:47,722 --> 01:18:49,471
I see things that aren't there.

1414
01:18:49,597 --> 01:18:54,471
And sometimes I write about it
in my journal and talk about it

1415
01:18:54,597 --> 01:18:56,138
with people who can help me.

1416
01:18:57,346 --> 01:18:59,221
So you didn't really chop off
the clown's head

1417
01:18:59,346 --> 01:19:01,221
with the magical sword?

1418
01:19:01,263 --> 01:19:01,971
No.

1419
01:19:02,971 --> 01:19:05,471
Damn,
that would've been so cool.

1420
01:19:15,138 --> 01:19:16,847
Gabs.

1421
01:19:16,889 --> 01:19:20,096
You have to promise me
you're not gonna tell anyone

1422
01:19:20,138 --> 01:19:22,096
what you read
in my journal, okay?

1423
01:19:22,221 --> 01:19:24,471
Not your parents,
not your friends at school?

1424
01:19:24,513 --> 01:19:25,471
No one.

1425
01:19:25,513 --> 01:19:26,763
Promise me.

1426
01:19:27,471 --> 01:19:29,096
I promise.

1427
01:19:30,096 --> 01:19:31,638
Pinky swear.

1428
01:19:35,847 --> 01:19:37,221
Okay.

1429
01:19:37,597 --> 01:19:39,638
(TAKES A DEEP BREATH)

1430
01:19:41,138 --> 01:19:43,096
Let's play Pictionary
so I can kick your ass.

1431
01:19:43,221 --> 01:19:44,638
(CHUCKLES)

1432
01:19:49,597 --> 01:19:50,889
COLE:
You're probably
still passed out.

1433
01:19:50,971 --> 01:19:54,597
Uh, look, I just wanted
to call and see if...

1434
01:19:54,638 --> 01:19:55,388
...you're okay, man?

1435
01:19:55,471 --> 01:19:56,597
Um...

1436
01:19:56,638 --> 01:19:57,722
Yeah.

1437
01:19:57,847 --> 01:19:59,346
Gimme a call back whenever
you get this, but, uh,

1438
01:19:59,471 --> 01:20:02,471
if you can't reach me,
I'll be at the Beta bash, so...

1439
01:20:02,597 --> 01:20:03,889
Peace.

1440
01:20:05,138 --> 01:20:07,889
You don't think I was that
insensitive before, do you?

1441
01:20:07,971 --> 01:20:09,847
Uh, yes.

1442
01:20:09,889 --> 01:20:11,513
Yes, I do actually.

1443
01:20:11,597 --> 01:20:13,221
Okay, I get
it's like a touchy subject

1444
01:20:13,346 --> 01:20:15,471
and all, but come on,
it didn't happen yesterday.

1445
01:20:15,597 --> 01:20:16,763
It happened five years ago.

1446
01:20:16,847 --> 01:20:18,138
Yeah, I don't think
that's something

1447
01:20:18,221 --> 01:20:19,763
you ever really get over.

1448
01:20:19,847 --> 01:20:22,346
Well, she still didn't mean
to snap at me the way she did.

1449
01:20:23,013 --> 01:20:25,138
Besides, talking it out
is good therapy.

1450
01:20:25,221 --> 01:20:27,346
I was basically doing
her a favor.

1451
01:20:27,388 --> 01:20:29,722
COLE:
Wow, how selfless of you.

1452
01:20:30,722 --> 01:20:32,263
Well, what about Jonathan?

1453
01:20:32,346 --> 01:20:34,597
Do you think he'd still be
willing to do it?

1454
01:20:35,471 --> 01:20:36,263
(COLE CHUCKLES)

1455
01:20:36,346 --> 01:20:37,971
I don't know, Mia.

1456
01:20:38,096 --> 01:20:39,388
(CHUCKLES)

1457
01:20:39,471 --> 01:20:41,513
Cole,
I want that interview.

1458
01:20:41,597 --> 01:20:42,722
I mean, sitting across
from someone

1459
01:20:42,763 --> 01:20:45,263
who actually encountered
Art the Clown?

1460
01:20:45,722 --> 01:20:48,138
The most famous serial killer
since Jack the Ripper.

1461
01:20:48,221 --> 01:20:49,847
It's historic.

1462
01:20:49,889 --> 01:20:50,847
COLE:
'Encountered.'

1463
01:20:50,889 --> 01:20:53,597
That's putting it mildly,
wouldn't you say?

1464
01:20:53,722 --> 01:20:55,263
The kid was almost butchered.

1465
01:20:55,346 --> 01:20:57,346
You know what I mean.

1466
01:20:58,138 --> 01:20:59,971
I want to know
what it's like to be

1467
01:21:00,013 --> 01:21:02,722
in the presence
of that kind of evil.

1468
01:21:04,013 --> 01:21:05,471
What goes through
your brain

1469
01:21:05,513 --> 01:21:08,221
when he's close enough to you
that you feel his breath

1470
01:21:08,346 --> 01:21:09,971
on your body?

1471
01:21:10,013 --> 01:21:11,763
What does he smell like?

1472
01:21:12,471 --> 01:21:13,388
(CLOWNY SNIFFS)

1473
01:21:13,471 --> 01:21:14,513
MIA:
When you look into his eyes.

1474
01:21:14,597 --> 01:21:15,221
What do you see?

1475
01:21:15,346 --> 01:21:17,971
Is there a soul or...

1476
01:21:19,597 --> 01:21:20,138
(LAUGHS)

1477
01:21:20,221 --> 01:21:21,847
'His eyes!'

1478
01:21:22,722 --> 01:21:23,971
You sound like
you want to fuck him.

1479
01:21:24,013 --> 01:21:25,346
I don't want to fuck him.

1480
01:21:27,763 --> 01:21:30,221
I mean,
you're friendly with Jonathan.

1481
01:21:30,346 --> 01:21:32,013
You said he looks
up to you, right?

1482
01:21:32,096 --> 01:21:34,013
Maybe you can convince him
for me,

1483
01:21:34,096 --> 01:21:35,096
Mia...

1484
01:21:35,138 --> 01:21:37,263
MIA:
Come on.

1485
01:21:37,346 --> 01:21:39,597
Do it for me.

1486
01:21:39,722 --> 01:21:41,013
Please?

1487
01:21:41,971 --> 01:21:44,597
I'll be nice,
I promise.

1488
01:21:44,722 --> 01:21:45,597
COLE:
Mhm.

1489
01:21:45,722 --> 01:21:48,346
All I need is 20 minutes,
tops.

1490
01:21:48,471 --> 01:21:49,847
(GIGGLES)

1491
01:21:49,971 --> 01:21:52,013
I'll make it worth your while.

1492
01:21:53,471 --> 01:21:54,971
(COLE SIGHS)

1493
01:21:55,096 --> 01:21:58,096
(KISSING)

1494
01:22:01,346 --> 01:22:05,013
Oh, wow.

1495
01:22:05,096 --> 01:22:06,221
You are very persuasive.

1496
01:22:06,263 --> 01:22:07,263
(CHUCKLES)

1497
01:22:07,346 --> 01:22:08,847
(MOANING)

1498
01:22:08,971 --> 01:22:11,847
COLE:
I'll see what I can do.

1499
01:22:11,971 --> 01:22:13,221
(KISSING)

1500
01:22:15,638 --> 01:22:17,221
Okay, so remind me
how to play this again.

1501
01:22:17,263 --> 01:22:18,221
It's been a while.

1502
01:22:18,263 --> 01:22:18,889
Wait.

1503
01:22:18,971 --> 01:22:21,013
We need more players.

1504
01:22:21,096 --> 01:22:22,763
Dad, come on.

1505
01:22:22,847 --> 01:22:25,263
NEWS ANCHOR: (ON TV)
...casualties after an explosion
rocks the Centerville Mall

1506
01:22:25,346 --> 01:22:27,096
just outside of Miles County.

1507
01:22:27,138 --> 01:22:28,388
Dad?

1508
01:22:28,471 --> 01:22:30,722
Again, five people have been
declared dead at this time

1509
01:22:30,763 --> 01:22:33,346
and six
are in critical condition.

1510
01:22:33,471 --> 01:22:35,722
The explosion happened
around 5pm this afternoon

1511
01:22:35,763 --> 01:22:38,722
at the Centerville Mall,
as the children gathered around

1512
01:22:38,763 --> 01:22:40,471
the holiday center display.

1513
01:22:40,597 --> 01:22:42,722
No suspects are in custody
at this time,

1514
01:22:42,763 --> 01:22:45,847
as the investigation
is still underway.

1515
01:22:45,971 --> 01:22:46,722
Close?

1516
01:22:46,847 --> 01:22:48,847
I was pretty damn close!

1517
01:22:48,971 --> 01:22:50,722
Too close for my liking.

1518
01:22:50,763 --> 01:22:51,889
Was it a terrorist attack?

1519
01:22:51,971 --> 01:22:52,971
I don't know, baby.

1520
01:22:53,096 --> 01:22:54,346
BYSTANDER: (ON TV)
Anyway, here's what I saw.

1521
01:22:54,388 --> 01:22:55,971
There was this guy, and he
was dressed as Santa Claus,

1522
01:22:56,013 --> 01:22:57,889
and he was handing out
presents to kids.

1523
01:22:57,971 --> 01:22:59,722
Every little kid that was there.

1524
01:22:59,763 --> 01:23:01,763
I heard a commotion,
and then I saw security

1525
01:23:01,847 --> 01:23:02,638
leading the guy out.

1526
01:23:02,722 --> 01:23:03,597
And then, bam!

1527
01:23:03,722 --> 01:23:05,722
There was an explosion
right there.

1528
01:23:05,763 --> 01:23:06,722
Holy shit.

1529
01:23:06,847 --> 01:23:10,096
He's here, he's here.

1530
01:23:10,221 --> 01:23:11,096
It's not safe.

1531
01:23:11,221 --> 01:23:12,013
It's not safe.

1532
01:23:12,096 --> 01:23:15,096
(PANTS)

1533
01:23:15,763 --> 01:23:16,847
SIENNA:
It's not safe.

1534
01:23:16,971 --> 01:23:17,847
It's not safe.

1535
01:23:17,889 --> 01:23:19,013
Sienna,
what are you talking about?

1536
01:23:19,096 --> 01:23:21,138
The Miles County Clown.

1537
01:23:21,221 --> 01:23:23,346
I saw-- I saw him today.

1538
01:23:23,471 --> 01:23:23,971
Listen to me.

1539
01:23:24,096 --> 01:23:25,013
No, I saw him today.

1540
01:23:25,096 --> 01:23:26,722
-GREG: All right.
-Okay, I saw him.

1541
01:23:26,847 --> 01:23:28,013
And I wasn't gonna say
anything

1542
01:23:28,096 --> 01:23:29,221
because I knew
you wouldn't believe me.

1543
01:23:29,346 --> 01:23:29,971
GREG:
Okay.

1544
01:23:30,096 --> 01:23:31,971
And he's gonna come for us.

1545
01:23:32,013 --> 01:23:33,388
-No, honey. No.
-He's gonna come.

1546
01:23:33,471 --> 01:23:34,638
GREG:
All right.

1547
01:23:34,722 --> 01:23:36,388
We have to get-- As long as
I'm here, we're in danger.

1548
01:23:36,471 --> 01:23:37,513
Okay? We're in danger.

1549
01:23:37,597 --> 01:23:39,388
We have to get as far away
from here as possible.

1550
01:23:39,471 --> 01:23:40,971
There's no Miles County Clown,
Sienna.

1551
01:23:41,096 --> 01:23:42,346
No, it was him, okay?

1552
01:23:42,471 --> 01:23:43,513
I saw him.

1553
01:23:43,597 --> 01:23:44,346
-GREG: Nobody's coming for--
-SIENNA: Listen to me.

1554
01:23:44,471 --> 01:23:45,013
JESSICA:
Stop it!

1555
01:23:45,096 --> 01:23:45,971
You are scaring Gabbie.

1556
01:23:46,013 --> 01:23:46,513
Stop it!

1557
01:23:46,597 --> 01:23:47,388
SIENNA:
Jonathan!

1558
01:23:47,471 --> 01:23:48,346
Jonathan!
We have to call Jonathan.

1559
01:23:48,388 --> 01:23:49,513
I will call Jonathan.

1560
01:23:49,597 --> 01:23:51,763
If they know-- Jonathan,
then we have to call Jonathan,

1561
01:23:51,847 --> 01:23:53,096
right now.

1562
01:23:55,096 --> 01:23:57,971
(PHONE RINGING)

1563
01:24:09,095 --> 01:24:10,262
Hey, Uncle Greg.

1564
01:24:10,345 --> 01:24:11,387
Jonathan.

1565
01:24:11,470 --> 01:24:14,345
Dude, your sister
is freaking out over here, man.

1566
01:24:14,387 --> 01:24:15,888
She saw something on the news,

1567
01:24:15,970 --> 01:24:17,470
and she's adamant
about getting you over here

1568
01:24:17,512 --> 01:24:19,095
as soon as possible.

1569
01:24:20,137 --> 01:24:21,970
She thinks you're in danger.

1570
01:24:26,220 --> 01:24:27,637
What'd she see?

1571
01:24:27,721 --> 01:24:30,596
She saw the news, man,
about the explosion.

1572
01:24:30,637 --> 01:24:33,220
Look, I think a few people
were killed, and now she's--

1573
01:24:33,262 --> 01:24:33,970
Look, dude. It's bad.

1574
01:24:34,012 --> 01:24:35,470
I need to talk to him, okay?

1575
01:24:35,512 --> 01:24:36,137
Sienna!

1576
01:24:36,220 --> 01:24:37,470
Jonathan.

1577
01:24:37,596 --> 01:24:39,470
Oh! It's happening,
it's happening, okay?

1578
01:24:39,596 --> 01:24:41,512
You need to let Uncle Greg
come and get you right now.

1579
01:24:41,596 --> 01:24:42,512
You're not safe.

1580
01:24:42,596 --> 01:24:43,345
You're not safe.

1581
01:24:43,387 --> 01:24:44,137
(SNIFFLES)

1582
01:24:44,220 --> 01:24:46,262
Okay, I'll come over.

1583
01:24:49,012 --> 01:24:50,512
Did you get it?

1584
01:24:53,095 --> 01:24:54,970
Yeah, I got it.

1585
01:24:55,012 --> 01:24:56,470
(WHIMPERING)

1586
01:24:56,512 --> 01:24:57,970
See you soon.

1587
01:24:59,220 --> 01:25:00,012
Okay.

1588
01:25:10,846 --> 01:25:12,721
I gave her something
to help her sleep.

1589
01:25:12,846 --> 01:25:14,095
Good.

1590
01:25:15,345 --> 01:25:16,637
You were right.

1591
01:25:22,970 --> 01:25:24,846
We'll talk about it
when I get back.

1592
01:25:25,888 --> 01:25:27,846
Be careful.

1593
01:25:27,888 --> 01:25:29,637
Call me if anything.

1594
01:25:29,721 --> 01:25:32,721
(DOOR OPENS, CLOSES)

1595
01:25:33,846 --> 01:25:35,970
JESSICA:
Hey, sweetie.

1596
01:25:36,012 --> 01:25:36,970
You okay?

1597
01:25:37,970 --> 01:25:39,470
Where's Sienna?

1598
01:25:39,970 --> 01:25:41,721
She's sleeping.

1599
01:25:43,262 --> 01:25:44,846
(SIGHS)

1600
01:25:44,970 --> 01:25:48,721
She's gonna go back
to the hospital, isn't she?

1601
01:25:50,387 --> 01:25:52,470
I don't know, baby.

1602
01:25:52,512 --> 01:25:54,387
I don't want her to.

1603
01:25:54,470 --> 01:25:57,095
But if she's not well,
we gotta do what's best for her.

1604
01:25:59,220 --> 01:26:01,095
What if she's right?

1605
01:26:01,137 --> 01:26:02,846
What if the Miles County Clown
